# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloudflare Pages headers for hellodb.dev
#
# Two concerns:
#   1. Content-Type overrides for extension-less Next.js metadata routes
#      (social crawlers refuse to unfurl octet-stream)
#   2. Security headers applied site-wide — CSP, HSTS, frame-deny, etc.
#
# Blog post og:image lives at a dynamic path, so we glob to cover nested
# opengraph-image routes as well as the root.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Metadata routes — Content-Type overrides so X / Slack / Discord unfurl.
/opengraph-image
  Content-Type: image/png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600

/opengraph-image/
  Content-Type: image/png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600

/blog/*/opengraph-image
  Content-Type: image/png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600

/blog/*/opengraph-image/
  Content-Type: image/png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600

/icon
  Content-Type: image/png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400

/icon/
  Content-Type: image/png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400

# /_next/static/* long-cache rule removed — CF Pages applies its own
# sensible default (4h + immutable for hashed assets). A previous
# aspirational `max-age=31536000, immutable` rule here was merged by
# the edge with the site-wide `must-revalidate` and CF's default,
# producing a contradictory "immutable + must-revalidate" header mash.
# CF's default is correct; we let it pass.

# Site-wide security headers.
#
# CSP model:
#   - script-src 'self' blocks eval(), Function(), setTimeout("string")
#     — this is the strict gate that protects against inline-script XSS.
#   - script-src-elem 'self' 'unsafe-inline' allows <script> element
#     content specifically. The only inline <script> this site emits is
#     the JSON-LD metadata block in app/layout.tsx (type="application/
#     ld+json", not executable JS but still subject to CSP). Everything
#     else is external src= chunks under /_next/static/.
#   - style-src 'unsafe-inline' is needed for Next.js 16's inlined
#     critical CSS on initial paint; there's no escape hatch without
#     moving to SSR with nonces.
#
# If third-party analytics / fonts are ever added, widen the allowlist
# explicitly — do NOT revert script-src to 'unsafe-inline' wholesale.
#
# HSTS: max-age=63072000 (2y) + includeSubDomains only. Intentionally
# no `preload` token — that requires submission at hstspreload.org and
# advertising preload without submitting is misleading to scanners.
/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; script-src-elem 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https:; font-src 'self' data: https://fonts.gstatic.com; connect-src 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  X-Robots-Tag: index, follow
